# macOS creates a hidden file literally named Icon + a carriage return (Icon\r)
# when a folder has a custom icon. This entry must end with \r to match it — don't retype this line.
#
# WARNING: the \r is lost every time this file is edited, so always restore it after any change:
#   perl -i -pe 's/^Icon\n/Icon\r\n/' ~/.gitignore_global
#
# Verify with:
#   cat -A ~/.gitignore_global | grep Icon
# Expected output: Icon^M$  (^M = \r, $ = end of line — if you see just Icon$ it's broken)
Icon


